title: Maria Cantwell
deleted: The close 2004 gubernatorial race between Democrat [[Christine Gregoire]] and Republican [[Dino Rossi]] suggested to many that the 2006 contest might go either way.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.strategicvision.biz/political/washington_poll_0520.htm |title=Poll Results â€” WA |date=May 17, 2005 |access-date=November 7, 2006 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060613221738/http://www.strategicvision.biz/political/washington_poll_0520.htm |archive-date=June 13, 2006  }}</ref> Both Cantwell and her opponent Republican [[Mike McGavick]] dominated their primaries; initial speculation favored a Republican victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vote.wa.gov/Elections/PrimaryResults/Results.aspx?o=8f43af96-81c1-47c6-8b5f-3ad9dee0e6ad |title=2006 Primary Election Results |publisher=Washington Secretary of State |date=October 3, 2006 |access-date=November 7, 2006 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060923205848/http://vote.wa.gov/elections/PrimaryResults/Results.aspx?o=8f43af96-81c1-47c6-8b5f-3ad9dee0e6ad |archive-date=September 23, 2006 }}</ref> "At one point," wrote analyst [[Larry Sabato]], "all the talk in this race concerned Cantwell's cool relations with anti-war Democratic elements and McGavick's relatively united base. But Democrats appear to have closed ranks behind their junior senator."<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.centerforpolitics.org/crystalball/article.php?id=LJS2006092101 | title=September 19 Primary Updates | publisher=Center of Politics | access-date=November 7, 2006 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20061013222153/http://www.centerforpolitics.org/crystalball/article.php?id=LJS2006092101 <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archive-date = October 13, 2006}}</ref> Cantwell ended up winning re-election by a 16-point margin, even winning several traditionally Republican counties in Eastern Washington including [[Spokane County]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vote.wa.gov/Elections/general/Results.aspx?o=8f43af96-81c1-47c6-8b5f-3ad9dee0e6ad |title=2006 General Election Results |publisher=Washington Secretary of State |access-date=November 17, 2006 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061201103234/http://vote.wa.gov/Elections/general/Results.aspx?o=8f43af96-81c1-47c6-8b5f-3ad9dee0e6ad |archive-date=December 1, 2006  }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.cnn.com/ELECTION/2006/pages/results/states/WA/S/01/index.html | title=U.S. Senate, Washington | publisher=CNN | access-date=December 2, 2006}}</ref>
